Uses of Package
co.cask.coopr.spec

Packages that use co.cask.coopr.spec
co.cask.coopr.cluster Cluster and Node objects. 
co.cask.coopr.codec.json.current Codecs for serializing and deserializing current versions of objects to and from json. 
co.cask.coopr.http.request Http requests. 
co.cask.coopr.provisioner Classes for interacting with provisioners. 
co.cask.coopr.provisioner.plugin Classes for managing provisioner plugin data. 
co.cask.coopr.scheduler Schedules threads for solving cluster layouts and planning and coordinating cluster jobs and tasks. 
co.cask.coopr.scheduler.task Classes for coordinating tasks and jobs. 
co.cask.coopr.spec Specifications for admin definable entities. 
co.cask.coopr.spec.plugin Specifications for provisioner plugins. 
co.cask.coopr.spec.service Specifications for services. 
co.cask.coopr.spec.template Specifications for cluster templates. 
co.cask.coopr.store.entity Persistent store for admin definable entities. 
co.cask.coopr.store.tenant Persistent store for tenant information. 
 

Classes in co.cask.coopr.spec used by co.cask.coopr.cluster
Link
          Specification to expose a link at the cluster or node level.
NamedEntity
          A named entity has a name that must only consist of alphanumeric characters, underscore, period, and dash.
Provider
          Machine providers are instances of some ProviderType like openstack, aws, rackspace, or joyent that can provision machines.
 

Classes in co.cask.coopr.spec used by co.cask.coopr.codec.json.current
BaseEntity
          A base for entities that require a name and optionally support an icon, description, and label.
BaseEntity.Builder
          Base builder for creating admin entities.
HardwareType
          A hardware type defines some hardware that will be used when constructing a cluster, as well as a mapping to different providers and information needed by the provisioner to create the hardware for each provider, which should contain the provider specific flavor and any other information needed to create the hardware.
ImageType
          Image type defines different images to use on on clusters, and include information needed by provisioners to provision machines from different providers.
Provider
          Machine providers are instances of some ProviderType like openstack, aws, rackspace, or joyent that can provision machines.
Tenant
          A tenant contains the id, plus fields.
TenantSpecification
          A tenant as seen from external world, meaning it contains the name and settings for a tenant, but no id.
